content:
They robbed my heartrate and my words
every sentence I thought to speak
fell in and through the veil of speech
that drove my thoughts and varied ticks.
&ldquo;When&rsquo;d it start?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Think I was six&rdquo;.
&ldquo;And did the anxiolytics help?&rdquo;
&ldquo;They squashed my thoughts
and my nervous ticks&rdquo;
&ldquo;So why claim to me that they did not?&rdquo;
&ldquo;It helps me in the likeness that
you can come to help someone
at knifepoint
in the parking lot.&quot;

